The Khapra Beetle {
 Trogoderma granarium Everts (Coleoptera: Dermestidae)}, lesser grain borer {
 Rhyzopertha dominica (Fabricius) (Coleoptera: Bostrichidae)}, red flour beetle {
 Tribolium castaneum (Herbst) (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae)}, and saw-toothed grain beetle {
 Oryzaephilus surinamensis (L.) (Coleoptera: Silvanidae)} are among the most well-known and economically-important stored-product pests with world-wide distribution. Along with direct damage due to feeding on various stored products, the quality of products is strictly diminished because of their residues and mechanically associated microbes [
 1,
 2,
 3,
 4,
 5].
